<HEADLINE>
FT  26 FEB 94 / Finance and the Family: Weak month for inflows into unit
trusts - At a Glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
January was a relatively weak month for inflows into unit trusts although
they still retained their popularity with private investors. Net investment
of Pounds 490m was almost half the Pounds 895m invested in December. Autif,
the unit trust industry body, attributed the fall to heavy selling by
institutions in the Far East for profit-taking after last year's strong
performance in the region. Private investors accounted for a net Pounds 534m
investment last month. The most popular retail funds were international
growth and UK equity income funds.
</TEXT>
