<PROFILE>_AN-EB0AFADCFT</PROFILE>
<DATE>940226
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  26 FEB 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The markets for both black and white pepper have been steady and very active
over the past few days, reports Man Producten. as demand has continued from
dealers and grinders trying to cover their short positions. Black MG-1 was
quoted at USDollars 1,700 a tonne, cif, for March/April shipment, with spot
at Dollars 1,775. Grinding quality pepper, 500 grammes a litre, fetched
Dollars 1,475 a tonne on shipment, and Dollars 1,575 on the spot. Black
pepper faq was Dollars 1,525 a tonne, spot, and Dollars 1,450, cif for
nearby shipments. White muntok faq for March shipment was Dollars 2,825 a
tonne and on the spot Dollars 2,950.
