</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
North Broken Hill Peko, the Australian mining and exploration group,
yesterday reported a sharp rise in after-tax profit in the six months to the
end of December. The result was ADollars 86.4m (USDollars 63m), compared
with ADollars 52.3m in the same period of 1992/93, writes Nikki Tait in
