because there would be no contribution from the paper manufacturing and
distribution business sold to Amcor in November. Lower iron ore prices
negotiated with the Japanese steel mills would also affect the result.
These factors would be partly offset by improved contributions from gold
mining and the 66 per cent-owned Energy Resources of Australia.
