FT  26 FEB 94 / UK Company News: North of England BS falls 19%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALISON SMITH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
North of England Building Society yesterday announced a fall from Pounds
16.7m to Pounds 13.5m in pre-tax profits for the 1993 year.
The decline was against the trend of recent announcements in the sector
which have shown significantly increased profits.
The 19 per cent fall, struck after an exceptional profit of Pounds 1m from
the sale of its Sunderland headquarters, was due mainly to increased
provisions, totalling Pounds 2.58m, for mortgage losses and the need to
compensate customers of its independent financial advice service who
suffered as a result of mis-selling.
Gross mortgage advances fell to Pounds 168.4m (Pounds 288.5m). There were
reductions in net interest receivable at Pounds 25.9m (Pounds 26.7m) and
other income and charges at Pounds 6.9m (Pounds 7.37m). Total assets rose to
Pounds 1.51bn (Pounds 1.42bn).
