FT  26 FEB 94 / Letters to the Editor: Euro Conservatives: no links, similar
whips (2)
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr RICHARD SIMMONDS MEP
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Sir Teddy Taylor complains ('Tories split over European allies' federal
stance in poll manifesto') that British Conservative MPs are whipped along
Westminster lines in the Parliamentary Group of the European People's party.
I am proud that we are, because I introduced the system to our continental
colleagues. It is regularly used to our advantage, for example to defeat the
parliament's left-wing majority's 'no confidence' motion in the British
presidency of the council.
Of course, the whip does not have the same power and patronage as at
Westminster, because there is no European government to defend or bring
down.
From time to time all national sections of the EPP decline the group whip,
when their individual party or national interest is in conflict with it.
Long may that practice continue.
Richard Simmonds,
