FT  26 FEB 94 / Rugby captain rings the Liffe bell
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOEL KIBAZO
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Will Carling, England's rugby captain, yesterday rang the bell at the London
International Financial Futures and Options Exchange to signal the start of
trading in the FT-SE Mid-250 index futures contract, Joel Kibazo writes. The
new contract is a rival to the Mid-250 futures contract which started
trading on the screen-based OMLX exchange three weeks ago. One dealer said
the Mid-250's first day of trading, with a total of 617 contracts dealt, had
been 'slightly disappointing'.
Next to Mr Carling is Mr Nick Durlacher, Liffe chairman, and immediately in
front of him is Mr Daniel Hodson, chief executive of the exchange, who said
the contract would enable investors to manage their exposure to all of the
UK's 350.
